snippet.textDisplay:
* Paper:
Camaro 650hp / 3892lbs = 5.98lbs x 1hp
Challenger 797hp / 4527lbs 5.68lbs x 1hp
Mustang 760hp / 4058lbs 5.33lbs x 1hp

According to the numbers on paper, in the weight - power ratio, the Camaro is in third place, the Challenger in second place and the Mustang in the first place, the difference in the weight - power ratio between each car is only 0.30lb per horse.

* 1/4 mile run from 0:
Mustang 1st place
Camaro 2nd place
Challenger 3rd place

There are two cars of difference between the Mustang and the Camaro and only one car of difference between the Camaro and the Challenger, but, why does the Camaro beat the Challenger if the Challenger has a better weight - power ratio ?, simple, mainly because the Camaro, like the Mustang, has a greater technological load than the Challenger, which helps it to be more stable and have a better grip on the floor when it takes off, if the Challenger had that, it would surely also be in second place, as its power weight - power ratio, for that reason I would have liked to see a roll race in this video too, in a roll race, the stability and grip on the floor does not matter as much as in a race from 0, in that case the things between the Challenger and the Camaro would surely have been different, the Challenger would have been in second place and the Camaro in third place, and in general there would only have been a difference of a car between each place.

In conclusion, the three are incredible cars in all aspects, although they are not exactly the same or the same segment, as the years go by the differences between these three cars and their predecessors are increasing, the Camaro and the Mustang are now american sports cars with a muscle / pony appearance but with similar handling in several respects to european sports cars, more the Camaro than the Mustang, the Mustang is a bit more aggressive and less stable in handling than the Camaro, the Mustang still in handling looks like an American sports car, the Camaro has become an extremely easy to drive car considering what it was before, what a real muscle/pony car is, and that it is a tall american sports car performance, also between these two cars there is a marked difference in comfort and practicality, the Mustang is notoriously larger than the Camaro, on the other hand, the Challenger is practically punctual and apart, is the car that has remained true to its roots, both in handling, sensations, size, performance and appearance, thanks to that, as the years go by, the Challenger becomes increasingly special, striking and desired, the Challenger remains the only true muscle car that can be obtained today.
